Nenad MedvidoviÄ‡ is a Professor of Computer Science and Informatics at the University of Southern California, Los Angeles. He is a fellow of the IEEE and an ACM Distinguished Scientist. He is chair of ACM SIGSOFT and co-author of Software Architecture: Foundations, Theory, and Practice (2009). In 2008, he received the Most Influential Paper Award for a paper titled "Architecture-Based Runtime Software Evolution" published in the ACM/IEEE International Conference on Software Engineering 1998.  In 2017, he received an IEEE International Conference on Software Architecture Best Paper Award for his paper titled "Continuous Analysis of Collaborative Design".


